analysis: The agent used "Saturday" for the dayOfWeek parameter instead of the expected "Sunday," not matching the ground truth. This mismatch in parameter value led to the evaluator not recognizing the function call as correct.

The failure was due to a case mismatch in the parameter values ("Millennials" and "Fitness" vs. "millennials" and "fitness"); the evaluator expected all-lowercase values while the model preserved capitalization.

The agent included an extra "targetAudience" parameter in the function call, which is not part of the expected input schema. This caused the evaluator to reject the call as a mismatch with the defined TemplateRecommender_suggestTemplates signature.
The agent sent the argument "imageCount" as a string ("10") instead of an integer (10), leading to a type mismatch and preventing function call matching as required by the evaluator.

The agent failed to invoke the OnlineFitnessClass_register tool and instead responded with clarifying questions, missing the opportunity to directly register the user for the requested yoga class as required.

The agent omitted required parameters ("apiKey" and "refreshRate") in the function call to GlobalAirQuality_queryCities, resulting in no match with the expected function signature and failure to execute the query as specified.
The agent omitted the required "comparisonType": "year-over-year" parameter in the CityPriceData_fetchAndCompare function call, resulting in a parameter mismatch with the expected function signature.

The agent used "Technology" (capitalized) in sectorList instead of the expected lowercase "technology," causing a mismatch with the evaluator's case-sensitive parameter check. The function call was otherwise structurally correct.
